1 hour ago, The Flying Kerbal said:

Very disappointed with you... you only have it a few minutes and you're already cheating!!?  

It's called 'TESTING'.  Tempting fate so we don't have to.

1. Mk1 capsule with Jeb on the KSC launchpad.
2. Alt-F12 → "Cheats" → "Jool" → "Set orbit" → (red error messagem the altitude is autocorrected) →"Set orbit"
3. Jool. But no visible capsule. IVA view works, "EVA" works.
4. Get invisible Jeb to EVA. Proper menu ("board" and so on) but neither capsule, nor Jeb.
5, Alt-F12 → add one zero to the altitude → Set Orbit. Still nothing.
6. Jeb → EVA, release. No visible Jeb or capsule.

Win 7 x64, No mods, pure install.

We're glad you're excited, people, but the rules about expletives still apply.

Bugs I found at least in VAB.

 

  • Grenade style capsules (Soviet styles from MH) don't show under silver variant fairings unless you look between the halves when hovering the mouse on them. Mk1 capsule show as usual. Relay antennas don't show as well, so suffice to say that some parts have difficuties to show under silver fairings.
  • Mk2 lander can has a context menu bug where the 'invert flag' shows on round capsule variant instead of 'toggle payload bay doors'. Unable to open those doors now. Thanks Squad you ruined the Mk2 lander can. Unable to open them in flight mode as well. Is this a problem for English localization as well as French?

These are the two bugs I found for now.
